text: Anticrates phaedima is a moth of the Lacturidae family. It is known from Australia, including Queensland. The wingspan is about 18 mm. Adults have whitish-yellow forewings with dark fuscous markings. The hindwings are red, but become paler towards the base.Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales ==References== Category:Zygaenoidea
title: Anticrates phaedima
